{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RC8qpRFhPNvPi1dzGc3554","type":"tool_result","content":"# Single-Component Protocol: Step-by-Step\n\n## Phase 1: Context & Recipe Selection\n\n1. **Identify the component's surface** — is this for application UI, marketing, commerce, docs, or another domain?\n2. **Check llms.txt** at `https://ui.askewly.com/llms.txt` for a matching recipe in the Recipes section.\n3. **If a recipe exists:** fetch it and use its Structure, Tokens, States, Checks, and Anti-patterns sections as your blueprint.\n4. **If no recipe exists:** fetch `docs/design-system/recipe-format.md` as your completeness checklist (intent, anatomy, tokens, states, checks, anti-patterns).\n\n## Phase 2: Token Judgment\n\n5. **Check the project's own design system first.** If the project owns a DESIGN.md, token SSOT, or established styling, derive every value from that source.\n6. **Only fetch** `https://ui.askewly.com/llms/tokens/tokens.css` **if:** the project has no tokens at all, OR the user explicitly requests Askewly Design. Never invent color or dimension values either way.\n7. **Paste the fetched tokens.css block once** at the top of your file; reference only semantic tokens (`var(--…)`) throughout the component code.\n\n## Phase 3: Anti-Pattern & Principle Review\n\n8. **Fetch** `https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/anti-patterns.md` and diagnose what generic-AI outputs look like; ensure your component avoids them.\n9. **Fetch** `https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/principles.md` and apply task-first hierarchy and meaningful motion in your implementation.\n\n## Phase 4: Implementation\n\n10. **Implement all interaction states first:** hover, focus, active, disabled, loading, error.\n11. **Complete the keyboard and ARIA contract** before visual refinement.\n\n## Phase 5: Self-Judgment (Mandatory)\n\n12. **Fetch** `https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/style-signature.md` and judge your finished output against all 5 operating principles.\n13. **Verify:** interaction states complete, dark mode holds, WCAG contrast passes.\n14. **Self-assessment must include per-principle judgment;** incomplete reports lack this step.\n\n## Phase 6: Human Verification Gate\n\n15. **Capture screenshots** (light and dark modes at minimum; include key states if applicable).\n16. **Attach file paths/images to your report** and **wait for human confirmation** — do not declare completion or deploy until the user has reviewed and approved the visual result.\n\n---\n\n**Critical rule:** Self-judgment is *the floor, not the ceiling.* Only human eyes settle whether the work \"actually looks good.\""}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"05f608d7-b1fc-4ad3-a101-9110f925f986","uuid":"a4f16e4a-2f47-4e5c-a5fc-40529cc916fc","timestamp":"2026-07-18T12:31:34.924Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":5438,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Single-Component Protocol: Step-by-Step\n\n## Phase 1: Context & Recipe Selection\n\n1. **Identify the component's surface** — is this for application UI, marketing, commerce, docs, or another domain?\n2. **Check llms.txt** at `https://ui.askewly.com/llms.txt` for a matching recipe in the Recipes section.\n3. **If a recipe exists:** fetch it and use its Structure, Tokens, States, Checks, and Anti-patterns sections as your blueprint.\n4. **If no recipe exists:** fetch `docs/design-system/recipe-format.md` as your completeness checklist (intent, anatomy, tokens, states, checks, anti-patterns).\n\n## Phase 2: Token Judgment\n\n5. **Check the project's own design system first.** If the project owns a DESIGN.md, token SSOT, or established styling, derive every value from that source.\n6. **Only fetch** `https://ui.askewly.com/llms/tokens/tokens.css` **if:** the project has no tokens at all, OR the user explicitly requests Askewly Design. Never invent color or dimension values either way.\n7. **Paste the fetched tokens.css block once** at the top of your file; reference only semantic tokens (`var(--…)`) throughout the component code.\n\n## Phase 3: Anti-Pattern & Principle Review\n\n8. **Fetch** `https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/anti-patterns.md` and diagnose what generic-AI outputs look like; ensure your component avoids them.\n9. **Fetch** `https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/principles.md` and apply task-first hierarchy and meaningful motion in your implementation.\n\n## Phase 4: Implementation\n\n10. **Implement all interaction states first:** hover, focus, active, disabled, loading, error.\n11. **Complete the keyboard and ARIA contract** before visual refinement.\n\n## Phase 5: Self-Judgment (Mandatory)\n\n12. **Fetch** `https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/style-signature.md` and judge your finished output against all 5 operating principles.\n13. **Verify:** interaction states complete, dark mode holds, WCAG contrast passes.\n14. **Self-assessment must include per-principle judgment;** incomplete reports lack this step.\n\n## Phase 6: Human Verification Gate\n\n15. **Capture screenshots** (light and dark modes at minimum; include key states if applicable).\n16. **Attach file paths/images to your report** and **wait for human confirmation** — do not declare completion or deploy until the user has reviewed and approved the visual result.\n\n---\n\n**Critical rule:** Self-judgment is *the floor, not the ceiling.* Only human eyes settle whether the work \"actually looks good.\"","durationMs":8407,"url":"https://ui.askewly.com/llms/docs/design-system/entry-protocol.md"}}
